# Hand-crafted Wikidata N-Triples fixture for the Phase 118b dump-streaming
# build script (scripts/build_wikidata_index.py). Covers seven well-known
# entities — the Phase 118 manual-validation set — plus the minimal
# scaffolding (P279 edges, type-entity nodes) needed to exercise the
# transitive-closure + bucket-evaluation logic end-to-end without
# downloading the full ~43 GB latest-truthy.nt.bz2.
#
# Sort order: lexicographic by subject URI. The streaming algorithm in
# build_wikidata_index.py groups consecutive triples by subject and asserts
# each subject is seen exactly once, so this ordering is load-bearing.
# When adding entries, sort the resulting file with `LC_ALL=C sort -u`
# to preserve byte-stable test runs.
#
# Coverage map (entity → bucket(s) → why this fixture entry exists):
#   Q4093  Olaf Scholz       politicians                p31_any [Q5] + p106_any [Q82955]
#   Q1124  Friedrich Merz    politicians                p31_any [Q5] + p106_any [Q82955]
#   Q325817 Tagesschau       broadcasters               p31 → Q1616075 (P279* → Q15265344)
#   Q3168143 Bundesregierung government_agencies        p31 → Q3624080 (P279* → Q327333)
#   Q1055  Bundestag         government_agencies        p31 → Q11204   (P279* → Q327333)
#   Q458   European Union    international_organizations p31 → Q1335818 (P279* → Q484652)
#   Q64    Berlin            cities_population_threshold p31 → Q1549591 (P279* → Q515) + P1082 ≥ 50k
#
# Negative control: Q9999 (a fictional concept) carries labels but no P31
# / P106 that maps to any bucket, and must NOT appear in the output index.

